result.execSummary:
Dylan Lance Young was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Dylan Lance Young was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 8:45 AM Defendant Dylan Lance Young appeared in person, in custody, Pro Se.. Attorney Kenneth N. Sortedahl appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Court reporter appears by zoom. Court calls case and recites appearances. DEF verifies his identity, agrees he is the person state of MN is looking for.  Court advised DEF of right to waive or contest extradition.  Court goes through waiver of extradition with DEF.  DEF waives extradition, signs extradition form.  Court certifies DEF has knowingly and voluntarily waived his right of extradition. Court signs extradition form and DEF is remanded to custody to await transport to MN.
State of MN - Warrant and Conditions of Release
EXTRADITION COMPLAINT PURSUANT TO WIS. STAT. 976.03(13)
